                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 31
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 does not contain the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters, but space was left for them to be written
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#17r #21r #24r #30r #32v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#17r #21r #35r #35v #39r"/>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (┬) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#161r"/>, line 7; <locus target="#161v"/>, line 6; <locus target="#162r"/>, line 6);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#1v #2r #9r #15r #16r"/>, etc.).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
